description:
Service Usage

This Service is invoked when VPO wants to perform below operations
readme:
Service Usage

This Service is invoked when VPO wants to perform below operations
Cancellation of visa
Undo Cancellation
Revoke Cancellation
undo set-aside or revoke or Reinstatement of visa (Reactivate Visa)
Withdraw
Undo Withdraw
Refuse Visa
Undo Refuse Visa
Invalid Visa
Undo Invalid Visa
Incorrect Grant of Visa
After operation is performed in TRIPS, TRIPS will then recalculate the Person's Lawful status.

Service Behaviour

The consumer triggers this service with the decision type and the details that are required to call TRIPS. ESB performs transformation into TRIPS request which is a flat file and routes to TRIPS. Response from TRIPS which is a flat file is transformed into XML and returned to Consumer.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

This service does not perform any enforcing actions like schema validation, but only passes the request message to ICSE.

Service Composition

Service Flow

An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the Modify Visa Status service on the ESB;
ESB Validate the request message sent by the consumer
when Consumer request having clientId, call to SV288 is made to transform ClientId to PersonId
ESB transforms the consumer request into TRIPS request which is a flat file and sends to TRIPS
TRIPS returns response to the ESB
ESB transforms the TRIPS response to Consumer response and returns to consumer.
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider raises an error.
ESB transforms Provider Error returned by TRIPS into Enterprise Error Message.
ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload.
Alternate Flow 2 (AF2)
If the service call was timeout, ESB should return SV329.MSG- E07 to the consumer.
Alternate Flow 3 (AF3)
The following alternate flow depicts the execution path that takes when call to SV288 fails.
ESB sends request to CDH thru SV288 to transform ClientId to PersonId.
SV288 service returns an exception in soap-xml.
ESB returns this exception to Consumer.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.
